to reclaim his body.

34
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:14,280
(Casting a spell)

35
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:32,160
Aunt Kate,

36
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:34,800
there's something you need to know.

37
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:36,120
What is it?

38
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:37,560
It's Siwat...

39
00:05:46,280 --> 00:05:47,160
Professor!

40
00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:30,040
That's...

41
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:31,560
what I was gonna tell you.

42
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:36,765
Siwat possesses powers
like Thara and Khunkhao do.

43
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:46,640
I'm sorry.

44
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:49,520
I really can't control it.

45
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:11,891
Are you sure that everything you told me,

46
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,080
about the four Brahmins

47
00:07:14,280 --> 00:07:16,080
and the powers you three possess,

48
00:07:16,900 --> 00:07:18,840
is connected to Tambralinga?

49
00:07:19,440 --> 00:07:20,960
All that we've witnessed

50
00:07:21,540 --> 00:07:23,360
leaves no room for doubt.

51
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:24,680
It's all real.

52
00:07:26,460 --> 00:07:27,760
The moment our noses bled,

53
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:30,840
it felt exactly like
the lightning that freed Kalakal.

54
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:32,561
He's been freed again, hasn't he?

55
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:36,200
We need to figure out
how to deal with him.

56
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:39,800
If he manages to possess...

57
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:40,920
any of us,

58
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:43,200
the rest will be in danger.

59
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:46,240
All of our past happened in Tambralinga.

60
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:48,888
Once we locate it,

61
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,960
we'll know how to deal with him.

62
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:53,720
Wait,

63
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:55,000
are you...

64
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:57,160
trying to find that city?

65
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:01,080
I think we need to do it.

66
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:01,924
You can't.

67
00:08:02,340 --> 00:08:03,840
If that city gets mentioned again,

68
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:06,160
treasure hunters
will come swarming into the forest.

69
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:07,700
If that's your concern,

70
00:08:07,740 --> 00:08:08,960
we promise we...

71
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,020
I'm worried that...

72
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:12,520
I'll lose my family again,
like I lost Singkhon.

73
00:08:18,540 --> 00:08:19,800
All of us...

74
00:08:20,420 --> 00:08:21,920
will be targeted.

75
00:08:22,420 --> 00:08:24,400
These treasure hunters will stop at nothing

76
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,960
to take the Shiva lingam and Yoni stone,

77
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:29,770
and everyone here will be at risk.

78
00:08:30,220 --> 00:08:32,380
What if we go in quietly?

79
00:08:34,040 --> 00:08:37,680
You know, just to find out
why the three of us had to meet again.

80
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:39,680
You've forgotten, haven't you,

81
00:08:40,460 --> 00:08:42,840
that Michael had to die

82
00:08:43,340 --> 00:08:44,440
because of that city?

83
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:45,360
Mom!

84
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:48,060
It took us ten long years

85
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:49,520
to come to terms with Singkhon's death.

86
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:52,800
Have you forgotten the agony we felt, Khun?

87
00:08:58,560 --> 00:09:00,960
I want you to start fresh

88
00:09:01,460 --> 00:09:02,720
and leave the past behind.

89
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:05,560
If we keep bringing up that city,

90
00:09:06,140 --> 00:09:07,520
how could Khun and Siwat

91
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:09,720
ever forget about Singkhon and Michael?

92
00:09:16,220 --> 00:09:17,520
But...

93
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:21,200
if you know full well that what you're after

94
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,640
will ruin everyone here,

95
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:25,920
and you still refuse to stop,

96
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:29,720
then I can't stop you.

97
00:09:30,940 --> 00:09:33,000
But if we're to suffer losses once again,

98
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:36,200
be prepared for the consequences.

99
00:10:19,340 --> 00:10:20,240
Who are you?

100
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:22,600
Why are you spying on my family?!

101
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:29,800
Nearly 20 years have passed,

102
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:33,280
and the lone huntress of Nakhon Si Thammarat

103
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:35,730
has become nothing more than a legend.

104
00:10:36,860 --> 00:10:37,760
Aisoon!

105
00:10:38,740 --> 00:10:39,960
What do you want?

106
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:42,720
Do you think Khunkhao will ever know

107
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:45,200
who was responsible

108
00:10:45,820 --> 00:10:46,960
for his dad's death?

109
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:48,240
Shut up!

110
00:10:49,020 --> 00:10:51,880
You'll need to beg me to keep quiet forever,

111
00:10:52,580 --> 00:10:53,720
like you always have.

112
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:55,597
Otherwise,

113
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:58,640
Khunkhao will hate you for life.

114
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:01,600
You already took Singkhon's life,

115
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:03,000
what more do you want?!

116
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:05,080
Bring me Siwat,

117
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:09,040
the Shiva lingam, and the Yoni Stone,

118
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:12,880
and I'll take this secret

119
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:14,400
to my grave.

120
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:35,840
Thara!

121
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:39,440
What?

122
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:43,600
Well,

123
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:46,160
I just wanted to say I'm sorry.

124
00:11:47,760 --> 00:11:49,400
If you're talking about the past,

125
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:51,520
it doesn't matter.

126
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:54,640
But I killed you with my own hands.

127
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:56,840
You didn't kill me.

128
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:58,920
Kalakal did.

129
00:12:05,860 --> 00:12:07,000
Don't worry about it.

130
00:12:08,920 --> 00:12:11,400
The more I see the past,

131
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:13,480
the more I fear...

132
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:16,945
that I might end up hurting you.

133
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:20,960
The past may have returned

134
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:23,400
so that we can deal with Kalakal.

135
00:12:24,680 --> 00:12:26,600
Uncle Singkhon once said that

136
00:12:27,160 --> 00:12:29,560
our deaths would mark the end of everything.

137
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:34,680
So today, I'll begin anew.

138
00:12:35,680 --> 00:12:38,240
I won't let the past
steal away the person I love,

139
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:40,920
or you, again.

140
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:46,260
I'm heading to bed now.

141
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:49,360
You should get some rest, too.

142
00:13:17,180 --> 00:13:18,809
I thought Thara would walk you here.

143
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:29,880
You've been through a lot today.

144
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:32,480
Go get some rest.

145
00:13:33,160 --> 00:13:34,327
Don't worry.

146
00:13:37,160 --> 00:13:37,840
Hang on.

147
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:46,800
Will you forgive my father?

148
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:57,920
I know it's not an easy thing to do...

149
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:02,160
